  "text": "where ∈ ( 1 , 2 ) and ( 1 , 2 ) denotes the family of all bounded linear operators 1 to 2 . In 1994, the SFP was first introduced by Censor and Elfving [CITATION_1] , in finite-dimensional Hilbert spaces, for modeling inverse problems which arise from phase retrievals and in medical image reconstruction. A number of image reconstruction problems can be formulated as the SFP; see, for example, [CITATION_2] and the references therein. Recently, it is found that the SFP can also be applied to study intensity modulated radiation therapy; see, for example, [CITATION_3] and the references therein.",
